In the provided build OS_DEBUG is defined as an empty macro (#define OS_DEBUG(__VA_ARGS__)). The debug invocation OS_DEBUG("Error: pthread_mutexattr_setprotocol failed: %s\n", strerror(ret)); therefore expands to nothing and has no runtime effect (strerror is not evaluated). Removing this statement would not affect program behaviour, so it constitutes dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. (If OS_DEBUG were defined to perform logging, then it would not be dead.)
